---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 30
By: Robert Herrick
Tags:
  - Creation=Inexhaustibility of the Creator
  - Life-Love=Charity=Mercy
---
Gods boundlesse mercy is (to sinfull man)
Like to the ever-wealthy Ocean：
Which though it sends forth thousand streams, ’tis ne’re
Known, or els seen to be the emptier：
And though it takes all in, ’tis yet no more
Full, and fild-full, then when full-fíld before.
